{
  "texts": [
    "While the current work targets the selective removal of a small number of unwanted tasks, future research will investigate strategies to efficiently handle discrimination between larger sets of similar tasks.",
    "Our current approach was largely inspired by the original LoRA paper (Hu et al., 2021), which was our motivation for only manipulating the attention weights.",
    "Subsequent research into LoRA revealed the effectiveness of manipulating the other layers within an LLM.",
    "Future works will explore the adaption of other layers to enhance the flexibility and performance of UNLEARN.",
    "This paper introduces UNLEARN, a novel approach for selectively forgetting knowledge in Large Language Models."
  ]
}